        <abstract> 
<p>On the <hi rend="italic">Fraser’s Magazine</hi> review by Hopkins [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">2860</hi>] and the <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Review</hi> article by Wilberforce ["Darwin’s <hi rend="italic">Origin of species</hi>", 108 (1860): 225–64]. The course of opinion since Oxford BAAS meeting. Asa Gray.</p>  
<p>Need for <hi rend="italic">Natural History Review</hi>, but fears it will be a burden for THH and lessen his original work. His own problem with work: if he had other duties he would be able to do absolutely nothing in science.</p> 
        </abstract>
